data.textUthmani: طه
data.wordByWord: طه [Ta Ha]
data.transliteration: Ta-ha

data.textUthmani: مَآ أَنزَلْنَا عَلَيْكَ ٱلْقُرْءَانَ لِتَشْقَىٰٓ
data.wordByWord: مَآ [Not] أَنزَلْنَا [We (have) sent down] عَلَيْكَ [to you] ٱلْقُرْءَانَ [the Quran] لِتَشْقَىٰٓ [that you be distressed]
data.transliteration: Ma anzalna AAalayka alqur-analitashqa

data.textUthmani: إِلَّا تَذْكِرَةً لِّمَن يَخْشَىٰ
data.wordByWord: إِلَّا [(But)] تَذْكِرَةًۭ [(as) a reminder] لِّمَن [for (those) who] يَخْشَىٰ [fear]
data.transliteration: Illa tathkiratan liman yakhsha

data.textUthmani: تَنزِيلًا مِّمَّنْ خَلَقَ ٱلْأَرْضَ وَٱلسَّمَـٰوَٰتِ ٱلْعُلَى
data.wordByWord: تَنزِيلًۭا [A revelation] مِّمَّنْ [from (He) Who] خَلَقَ [created] ٱلْأَرْضَ [the earth] وَٱلسَّمَـٰوَٰتِ [and the heavens] ٱلْعُلَى [[the] high]
data.transliteration: Tanzeelan mimman khalaqa al-arda wassamawatialAAula

data.textUthmani: ٱلرَّحْمَـٰنُ عَلَى ٱلْعَرْشِ ٱسْتَوَىٰ
data.wordByWord: ٱلرَّحْمَـٰنُ [The Most Gracious] عَلَى [over] ٱلْعَرْشِ [the Throne] ٱسْتَوَىٰ [is established]
data.transliteration: Arrahmanu AAalaalAAarshi istawa

data.textUthmani: لَهُۥ مَا فِى ٱلسَّمَـٰوَٰتِ وَمَا فِى ٱلْأَرْضِ وَمَا بَيْنَهُمَا وَمَا تَحْتَ ٱلثَّرَىٰ
data.wordByWord: لَهُۥ [To Him (belongs)] مَا [whatever] فِى [(is) in] ٱلسَّمَـٰوَٰتِ [the heavens] وَمَا [and whatever] فِى [(is) in] ٱلْأَرْضِ [the earth] وَمَا [and whatever] بَيْنَهُمَا [(is) between them] وَمَا [and whatever] تَحْتَ [(is) under] ٱلثَّرَىٰ [the soil]
data.transliteration: Lahu ma fee assamawatiwama fee al-ardi wama baynahuma wamatahta aththara

data.textUthmani: وَإِن تَجْهَرْ بِٱلْقَوْلِ فَإِنَّهُۥ يَعْلَمُ ٱلسِّرَّ وَأَخْفَى
data.wordByWord: وَإِن [And if] تَجْهَرْ [you speak aloud] بِٱلْقَوْلِ [the word] فَإِنَّهُۥ [then indeed, He] يَعْلَمُ [knows] ٱلسِّرَّ [the secret] وَأَخْفَى [and the more hidden]
data.transliteration: Wa-in tajhar bilqawli fa-innahuyaAAlamu assirra waakhfa

data.textUthmani: ٱللَّهُ لَآ إِلَـٰهَ إِلَّا هُوَ ۖ لَهُ ٱلْأَسْمَآءُ ٱلْحُسْنَىٰ
data.wordByWord: ٱللَّهُ [Allah ] لَآ [(there is) no] إِلَـٰهَ [god] إِلَّا [except] هُوَ ۖ [Him] لَهُ [To Him (belong)] ٱلْأَسْمَآءُ [the Names] ٱلْحُسْنَىٰ [the Most Beautiful]
data.transliteration: Allahu la ilaha illahuwa lahu al-asmao alhusna

data.textUthmani: وَهَلْ أَتَىٰكَ حَدِيثُ مُوسَىٰٓ
data.wordByWord: وَهَلْ [And has] أَتَىٰكَ [come to you] حَدِيثُ [the narration] مُوسَىٰٓ [(of) Musa]
data.transliteration: Wahal ataka hadeethu moosa

data.textUthmani: إِذْ رَءَا نَارًا فَقَالَ لِأَهْلِهِ ٱمْكُثُوٓا۟ إِنِّىٓ ءَانَسْتُ نَارًا لَّعَلِّىٓ ءَاتِيكُم مِّنْهَا بِقَبَسٍ أَوْ أَجِدُ عَلَى ٱلنَّارِ هُدًى
data.wordByWord: إِذْ [When] رَءَا [he saw] نَارًۭا [a fire] فَقَالَ [then he said] لِأَهْلِهِ [to his family] ٱمْكُثُوٓا۟ [Stay here] إِنِّىٓ [indeed, I] ءَانَسْتُ [[I] perceived] نَارًۭا [a fire] لَّعَلِّىٓ [perhaps I (can)] ءَاتِيكُم [bring you] مِّنْهَا [therefrom] بِقَبَسٍ [a burning brand] أَوْ [or] أَجِدُ [I find] عَلَى [at] ٱلنَّارِ [the fire] هُدًۭى [guidance]
data.transliteration: Ith raa naran faqalali-ahlihi omkuthoo innee anastu naran laAAallee ateekumminha biqabasin aw ajidu AAala annarihuda

data.textUthmani: فَلَمَّآ أَتَىٰهَا نُودِىَ يَـٰمُوسَىٰٓ
data.wordByWord: فَلَمَّآ [Then when] أَتَىٰهَا [he came to it] نُودِىَ [he was called] يَـٰمُوسَىٰٓ [O Musa]
data.transliteration: Falamma ataha noodiya yamoosa

data.textUthmani: إِنِّىٓ أَنَا۠ رَبُّكَ فَٱخْلَعْ نَعْلَيْكَ ۖ إِنَّكَ بِٱلْوَادِ ٱلْمُقَدَّسِ طُوًى
data.wordByWord: إِنِّىٓ [Indeed, [I]] أَنَا۠ [I Am] رَبُّكَ [your Lord] فَٱخْلَعْ [so remove] نَعْلَيْكَ ۖ [your shoes] إِنَّكَ [Indeed, you] بِٱلْوَادِ [(are) in the valley] ٱلْمُقَدَّسِ [the sacred] طُوًۭى [(of) Tuwa]
data.transliteration: Innee ana rabbuka fakhlaAAnaAAlayka innaka bilwadi almuqaddasi tuwa

data.textUthmani: وَأَنَا ٱخْتَرْتُكَ فَٱسْتَمِعْ لِمَا يُوحَىٰٓ
data.wordByWord: وَأَنَا [And I] ٱخْتَرْتُكَ [(have) chosen you] فَٱسْتَمِعْ [so listen] لِمَا [to what] يُوحَىٰٓ [is revealed]
data.transliteration: Waana ikhtartuka fastamiAAlima yooha

data.textUthmani: إِنَّنِىٓ أَنَا ٱللَّهُ لَآ إِلَـٰهَ إِلَّآ أَنَا۠ فَٱعْبُدْنِى وَأَقِمِ ٱلصَّلَوٰةَ لِذِكْرِىٓ
data.wordByWord: إِنَّنِىٓ [Indeed, [I]] أَنَا [I Am] ٱللَّهُ [Allah] لَآ [(There is) no] إِلَـٰهَ [god] إِلَّآ [but] أَنَا۠ [I] فَٱعْبُدْنِى [so worship Me] وَأَقِمِ [and establish] ٱلصَّلَوٰةَ [the prayer] لِذِكْرِىٓ [for My remembrance]
data.transliteration: Innanee ana Allahu lailaha illa ana faAAbudnee waaqimi assalatalithikree

data.textUthmani: إِنَّ ٱلسَّاعَةَ ءَاتِيَةٌ أَكَادُ أُخْفِيهَا لِتُجْزَىٰ كُلُّ نَفْسٍۭ بِمَا تَسْعَىٰ
data.wordByWord: إِنَّ [Indeed] ٱلسَّاعَةَ [the Hour] ءَاتِيَةٌ [(will be) coming] أَكَادُ [I almost] أُخْفِيهَا [[I] hide it] لِتُجْزَىٰ [that may be recompensed] كُلُّ [every] نَفْسٍۭ [soul] بِمَا [for what] تَسْعَىٰ [it strives]
data.transliteration: Inna assaAAata atiyatunakadu okhfeeha litujza kullu nafsin bimatasAAa

data.textUthmani: فَلَا يَصُدَّنَّكَ عَنْهَا مَن لَّا يُؤْمِنُ بِهَا وَٱتَّبَعَ هَوَىٰهُ فَتَرْدَىٰ
data.wordByWord: فَلَا [So (do) not] يَصُدَّنَّكَ [(let) avert you] عَنْهَا [from it] مَن [(one) who] لَّا [(does) not] يُؤْمِنُ [believe] بِهَا [in it] وَٱتَّبَعَ [and follows] هَوَىٰهُ [his desires] فَتَرْدَىٰ [lest you perish]
data.transliteration: Fala yasuddannaka AAanhaman la yu/minu biha wattabaAAa hawahufatarda

data.textUthmani: وَمَا تِلْكَ بِيَمِينِكَ يَـٰمُوسَىٰ
data.wordByWord: وَمَا [And what] تِلْكَ [(is) that] بِيَمِينِكَ [in your right hand] يَـٰمُوسَىٰ [O Musa]
data.transliteration: Wama tilka biyameenika ya moosa

data.textUthmani: قَالَ هِىَ عَصَاىَ أَتَوَكَّؤُا۟ عَلَيْهَا وَأَهُشُّ بِهَا عَلَىٰ غَنَمِى وَلِىَ فِيهَا مَـَٔارِبُ أُخْرَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] هِىَ [It] عَصَاىَ [(is) my staff] أَتَوَكَّؤُا۟ [I lean] عَلَيْهَا [upon it] وَأَهُشُّ [and I bring down leaves] بِهَا [with it] عَلَىٰ [for] غَنَمِى [my sheep] وَلِىَ [and for me] فِيهَا [in it] مَـَٔارِبُ [(are) uses] أُخْرَىٰ [other]
data.transliteration: Qala hiya AAasaya atawakkaoAAalayha waahushshu biha AAala ghanameewaliya feeha maaribu okhra

data.textUthmani: قَالَ أَلْقِهَا يَـٰمُوسَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] أَلْقِهَا [Throw it down] يَـٰمُوسَىٰ [O Musa]
data.transliteration: Qala alqiha ya moosa

data.textUthmani: فَأَلْقَىٰهَا فَإِذَا هِىَ حَيَّةٌ تَسْعَىٰ
data.wordByWord: فَأَلْقَىٰهَا [So he threw it down] فَإِذَا [and behold] هِىَ [It] حَيَّةٌۭ [(was) a snake] تَسْعَىٰ [moving swiftly]
data.transliteration: Faalqaha fa-itha hiya hayyatuntasAAa

data.textUthmani: قَالَ خُذْهَا وَلَا تَخَفْ ۖ سَنُعِيدُهَا سِيرَتَهَا ٱلْأُولَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] خُذْهَا [Seize it] وَلَا [and (do) not] تَخَفْ ۖ [fear] سَنُعِيدُهَا [We will return it] سِيرَتَهَا [(to) its state] ٱلْأُولَىٰ [the former]
data.transliteration: Qala khuthha walatakhaf sanuAAeeduha seerataha al-oola

data.textUthmani: وَٱضْمُمْ يَدَكَ إِلَىٰ جَنَاحِكَ تَخْرُجْ بَيْضَآءَ مِنْ غَيْرِ سُوٓءٍ ءَايَةً أُخْرَىٰ
data.wordByWord: وَٱضْمُمْ [And draw near] يَدَكَ [your hand] إِلَىٰ [to] جَنَاحِكَ [your side] تَخْرُجْ [it will come out] بَيْضَآءَ [white] مِنْ [without any] غَيْرِ [without any] سُوٓءٍ [disease] ءَايَةً [(as) a sign] أُخْرَىٰ [another]
data.transliteration: Wadmum yadaka ila janahikatakhruj baydaa min ghayri soo-in ayatan okhra

data.textUthmani: لِنُرِيَكَ مِنْ ءَايَـٰتِنَا ٱلْكُبْرَى
data.wordByWord: لِنُرِيَكَ [That We may show you] مِنْ [of] ءَايَـٰتِنَا [Our Signs] ٱلْكُبْرَى [the Greatest]
data.transliteration: Linuriyaka min ayatinaalkubra

data.textUthmani: ٱذْهَبْ إِلَىٰ فِرْعَوْنَ إِنَّهُۥ طَغَىٰ
data.wordByWord: ٱذْهَبْ [Go] إِلَىٰ [to] فِرْعَوْنَ [Firaun] إِنَّهُۥ [Indeed, he] طَغَىٰ [(has) transgressed]
data.transliteration: Ithhab ila firAAawna innahu tagha

data.textUthmani: قَالَ رَبِّ ٱشْرَحْ لِى صَدْرِى
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] رَبِّ [My Lord] ٱشْرَحْ [Expand] لِى [for me] صَدْرِى [my breast]
data.transliteration: Qala rabbi ishrah lee sadree

data.textUthmani: وَيَسِّرْ لِىٓ أَمْرِى
data.wordByWord: وَيَسِّرْ [And ease] لِىٓ [for me] أَمْرِى [my task]
data.transliteration: Wayassir lee amree

data.textUthmani: وَٱحْلُلْ عُقْدَةً مِّن لِّسَانِى
data.wordByWord: وَٱحْلُلْ [And untie] عُقْدَةًۭ [(the) knot] مِّن [from] لِّسَانِى [my tongue]
data.transliteration: Wahlul AAuqdatan min lisanee

data.textUthmani: يَفْقَهُوا۟ قَوْلِى
data.wordByWord: يَفْقَهُوا۟ [That they may understand] قَوْلِى [my speech]
data.transliteration: Yafqahoo qawlee

data.textUthmani: وَٱجْعَل لِّى وَزِيرًا مِّنْ أَهْلِى
data.wordByWord: وَٱجْعَل [And appoint] لِّى [for me] وَزِيرًۭا [a minister] مِّنْ [from] أَهْلِى [my family]
data.transliteration: WajAAal lee wazeeran min ahlee

data.textUthmani: هَـٰرُونَ أَخِى
data.wordByWord: هَـٰرُونَ [Harun] أَخِى [my brother]
data.transliteration: Haroona akhee

data.textUthmani: ٱشْدُدْ بِهِۦٓ أَزْرِى
data.wordByWord: ٱشْدُدْ [Reinforce] بِهِۦٓ [through him] أَزْرِى [my strength]
data.transliteration: Oshdud bihi azree

data.textUthmani: وَأَشْرِكْهُ فِىٓ أَمْرِى
data.wordByWord: وَأَشْرِكْهُ [And make him share] فِىٓ [[in]] أَمْرِى [my task]
data.transliteration: Waashrik-hu fee amree

data.textUthmani: كَىْ نُسَبِّحَكَ كَثِيرًا
data.wordByWord: كَىْ [That] نُسَبِّحَكَ [we may glorify You] كَثِيرًۭا [much]
data.transliteration: Kay nusabbihaka katheera

data.textUthmani: وَنَذْكُرَكَ كَثِيرًا
data.wordByWord: وَنَذْكُرَكَ [And [we] remember You] كَثِيرًا [much]
data.transliteration: Wanathkuraka katheera

data.textUthmani: إِنَّكَ كُنتَ بِنَا بَصِيرًا
data.wordByWord: إِنَّكَ [Indeed, [You]] كُنتَ [You are] بِنَا [of us] بَصِيرًۭا [All-Seer]
data.transliteration: Innaka kunta bina baseera

data.textUthmani: قَالَ قَدْ أُوتِيتَ سُؤْلَكَ يَـٰمُوسَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] قَدْ [Verily] أُوتِيتَ [you are granted] سُؤْلَكَ [your request] يَـٰمُوسَىٰ [O Musa]
data.transliteration: Qala qad ooteeta su/laka yamoosa

data.textUthmani: وَلَقَدْ مَنَنَّا عَلَيْكَ مَرَّةً أُخْرَىٰٓ
data.wordByWord: وَلَقَدْ [And indeed] مَنَنَّا [We conferred a favor] عَلَيْكَ [on you] مَرَّةً [another time] أُخْرَىٰٓ [another time]
data.transliteration: Walaqad mananna AAalayka marratanokhra

data.textUthmani: إِذْ أَوْحَيْنَآ إِلَىٰٓ أُمِّكَ مَا يُوحَىٰٓ
data.wordByWord: إِذْ [When] أَوْحَيْنَآ [We inspired] إِلَىٰٓ [to] أُمِّكَ [your mother] مَا [what] يُوحَىٰٓ [is inspired]
data.transliteration: Ith awhayna ilaommika ma yooha

data.textUthmani: أَنِ ٱقْذِفِيهِ فِى ٱلتَّابُوتِ فَٱقْذِفِيهِ فِى ٱلْيَمِّ فَلْيُلْقِهِ ٱلْيَمُّ بِٱلسَّاحِلِ يَأْخُذْهُ عَدُوٌّ لِّى وَعَدُوٌّ لَّهُۥ ۚ وَأَلْقَيْتُ عَلَيْكَ مَحَبَّةً مِّنِّى وَلِتُصْنَعَ عَلَىٰ عَيْنِىٓ
data.wordByWord: أَنِ [That] ٱقْذِفِيهِ [cast him] فِى [in] ٱلتَّابُوتِ [the chest] فَٱقْذِفِيهِ [then cast it] فِى [in] ٱلْيَمِّ [the river] فَلْيُلْقِهِ [then let cast it] ٱلْيَمُّ [the river] بِٱلسَّاحِلِ [on the bank] يَأْخُذْهُ [will take him] عَدُوٌّۭ [an enemy] لِّى [to Me] وَعَدُوٌّۭ [and an enemy] لَّهُۥ ۚ [to him] وَأَلْقَيْتُ [And I cast] عَلَيْكَ [over you] مَحَبَّةًۭ [love] مِّنِّى [from Me] وَلِتُصْنَعَ [and that you may be brought up] عَلَىٰ [under] عَيْنِىٓ [My eye]
data.transliteration: Ani iqthifeehi fee attabootifaqthifeehi fee alyammi falyulqihi alyammu bissahiliya/khuthhu AAaduwwun lee waAAaduwwun lahu waalqaytuAAalayka mahabbatan minnee walitusnaAAa AAalaAAaynee

words.translation: and that you may be brought up

data.textUthmani: إِذْ تَمْشِىٓ أُخْتُكَ فَتَقُولُ هَلْ أَدُلُّكُمْ عَلَىٰ مَن يَكْفُلُهُۥ ۖ فَرَجَعْنَـٰكَ إِلَىٰٓ أُمِّكَ كَىْ تَقَرَّ عَيْنُهَا وَلَا تَحْزَنَ ۚ وَقَتَلْتَ نَفْسًا فَنَجَّيْنَـٰكَ مِنَ ٱلْغَمِّ وَفَتَنَّـٰكَ فُتُونًا ۚ فَلَبِثْتَ سِنِينَ فِىٓ أَهْلِ مَدْيَنَ ثُمَّ جِئْتَ عَلَىٰ قَدَرٍ يَـٰمُوسَىٰ
data.wordByWord: إِذْ [When] تَمْشِىٓ [was going] أُخْتُكَ [your sister] فَتَقُولُ [and she said] هَلْ [Shall] أَدُلُّكُمْ [I show you] عَلَىٰ [[to]] مَن [(one) who] يَكْفُلُهُۥ ۖ [will nurse and rear him] فَرَجَعْنَـٰكَ [So We returned you] إِلَىٰٓ [to] أُمِّكَ [your mother] كَىْ [that] تَقَرَّ [may be cooled] عَيْنُهَا [her eyes] وَلَا [and not] تَحْزَنَ ۚ [she grieves] وَقَتَلْتَ [And you killed] نَفْسًۭا [a man] فَنَجَّيْنَـٰكَ [but We saved you] مِنَ [from] ٱلْغَمِّ [the distress] وَفَتَنَّـٰكَ [and We tried you] فُتُونًۭا ۚ [(with) a trial] فَلَبِثْتَ [Then you remained] سِنِينَ [(some) years] فِىٓ [with] أَهْلِ [(the) people] مَدْيَنَ [(of) Madyan] ثُمَّ [Then] جِئْتَ [you came] عَلَىٰ [at] قَدَرٍۢ [the decreed (time)] يَـٰمُوسَىٰ [O Musa]
data.transliteration: Ith tamshee okhtuka fataqoolu haladullukum AAala man yakfuluhu farajaAAnaka ilaommika kay taqarra AAaynuha wala tahzanawaqatalta nafsan fanajjaynaka mina alghammi wafatannakafutoonan falabithta sineena fee ahli madyana thumma ji/ta AAalaqadarin ya moosa

data.textUthmani: وَٱصْطَنَعْتُكَ لِنَفْسِى
data.wordByWord: وَٱصْطَنَعْتُكَ [And I (have) chosen you] لِنَفْسِى [for Myself]
data.transliteration: WastanaAAtuka linafsee

data.textUthmani: ٱذْهَبْ أَنتَ وَأَخُوكَ بِـَٔايَـٰتِى وَلَا تَنِيَا فِى ذِكْرِى
data.wordByWord: ٱذْهَبْ [Go] أَنتَ [you] وَأَخُوكَ [and your brother] بِـَٔايَـٰتِى [with My Signs] وَلَا [and (do) not] تَنِيَا [slacken] فِى [in] ذِكْرِى [My remembrance]
data.transliteration: Ithhab anta waakhooka bi-ayateewala taniya fee thikree

data.textUthmani: ٱذْهَبَآ إِلَىٰ فِرْعَوْنَ إِنَّهُۥ طَغَىٰ
data.wordByWord: ٱذْهَبَآ [Go, both of you] إِلَىٰ [to] فِرْعَوْنَ [Firaun] إِنَّهُۥ [Indeed, he] طَغَىٰ [(has) transgressed]
data.transliteration: Ithhaba ila firAAawnainnahu tagha

data.textUthmani: فَقُولَا لَهُۥ قَوْلًا لَّيِّنًا لَّعَلَّهُۥ يَتَذَكَّرُ أَوْ يَخْشَىٰ
data.wordByWord: فَقُولَا [And speak] لَهُۥ [to him] قَوْلًۭا [a word] لَّيِّنًۭا [gentle] لَّعَلَّهُۥ [perhaps he] يَتَذَكَّرُ [may take heed] أَوْ [or] يَخْشَىٰ [fear]
data.transliteration: Faqoola lahu qawlan layyinanlaAAallahu yatathakkaru aw yakhsha

data.textUthmani: قَالَا رَبَّنَآ إِنَّنَا نَخَافُ أَن يَفْرُطَ عَلَيْنَآ أَوْ أَن يَطْغَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالَا [They said] رَبَّنَآ [Our Lord] إِنَّنَا [Indeed, we] نَخَافُ [fear] أَن [that] يَفْرُطَ [he will hasten] عَلَيْنَآ [against us] أَوْ [or] أَن [that] يَطْغَىٰ [he will transgress]
data.transliteration: Qala rabbana innananakhafu an yafruta AAalayna aw an yatgha

data.textUthmani: قَالَ لَا تَخَافَآ ۖ إِنَّنِى مَعَكُمَآ أَسْمَعُ وَأَرَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] لَا [(Do) not] تَخَافَآ ۖ [fear] إِنَّنِى [Indeed, I Am] مَعَكُمَآ [with you both] أَسْمَعُ [I hear] وَأَرَىٰ [and I see]
data.transliteration: Qala la takhafainnanee maAAakuma asmaAAu waara

data.textUthmani: فَأْتِيَاهُ فَقُولَآ إِنَّا رَسُولَا رَبِّكَ فَأَرْسِلْ مَعَنَا بَنِىٓ إِسْرَٰٓءِيلَ وَلَا تُعَذِّبْهُمْ ۖ قَدْ جِئْنَـٰكَ بِـَٔايَةٍ مِّن رَّبِّكَ ۖ وَٱلسَّلَـٰمُ عَلَىٰ مَنِ ٱتَّبَعَ ٱلْهُدَىٰٓ
data.wordByWord: فَأْتِيَاهُ [So go to him] فَقُولَآ [and say] إِنَّا [Indeed, we] رَسُولَا [both (are) Messengers] رَبِّكَ [(of) your Lord] فَأَرْسِلْ [so send] مَعَنَا [with us] بَنِىٓ [(the) Children of Israel] إِسْرَٰٓءِيلَ [(the) Children of Israel] وَلَا [and (do) not] تُعَذِّبْهُمْ ۖ [torment them] قَدْ [Verily] جِئْنَـٰكَ [we came to you] بِـَٔايَةٍۢ [with a Sign] مِّن [from] رَّبِّكَ ۖ [your Lord] وَٱلسَّلَـٰمُ [And peace] عَلَىٰ [on] مَنِ [(one) who] ٱتَّبَعَ [follows] ٱلْهُدَىٰٓ [the Guidance]
data.transliteration: Fa/tiyahu faqoola innarasoola rabbika faarsil maAAana banee isra-eelawala tuAAaththibhum qad ji/naka bi-ayatinmin rabbika wassalamu AAala mani ittabaAAaalhuda

data.textUthmani: إِنَّا قَدْ أُوحِىَ إِلَيْنَآ أَنَّ ٱلْعَذَابَ عَلَىٰ مَن كَذَّبَ وَتَوَلَّىٰ
data.wordByWord: إِنَّا [Indeed, we] قَدْ [verily] أُوحِىَ [it has been revealed] إِلَيْنَآ [to us] أَنَّ [that] ٱلْعَذَابَ [the punishment] عَلَىٰ [(will be) on] مَن [(one) who] كَذَّبَ [denies] وَتَوَلَّىٰ [and turns away]
data.transliteration: Inna qad oohiya ilaynaanna alAAathaba AAala man kaththaba watawalla

data.textUthmani: قَالَ فَمَن رَّبُّكُمَا يَـٰمُوسَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] فَمَن [Then who] رَّبُّكُمَا [(is) your Lord] يَـٰمُوسَىٰ [O Musa]
data.transliteration: Qala faman rabbukuma yamoosa

data.textUthmani: قَالَ رَبُّنَا ٱلَّذِىٓ أَعْطَىٰ كُلَّ شَىْءٍ خَلْقَهُۥ ثُمَّ هَدَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] رَبُّنَا [Our Lord] ٱلَّذِىٓ [(is) the One Who] أَعْطَىٰ [gave] كُلَّ [(to) every] شَىْءٍ [thing] خَلْقَهُۥ [its form] ثُمَّ [then] هَدَىٰ [He guided (it)]
data.transliteration: Qala rabbuna allatheeaAAta kulla shay-in khalqahu thumma hada

data.textUthmani: قَالَ فَمَا بَالُ ٱلْقُرُونِ ٱلْأُولَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] فَمَا [Then what] بَالُ [(is the) case] ٱلْقُرُونِ [(of) the generations] ٱلْأُولَىٰ [(of) the former]
data.transliteration: Qala fama balualqurooni al-oola

data.textUthmani: قَالَ عِلْمُهَا عِندَ رَبِّى فِى كِتَـٰبٍ ۖ لَّا يَضِلُّ رَبِّى وَلَا يَنسَى
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] عِلْمُهَا [Its knowledge] عِندَ [(is) with] رَبِّى [my Lord] فِى [in] كِتَـٰبٍۢ ۖ [a Record] لَّا [Not] يَضِلُّ [errs] رَبِّى [my Lord] وَلَا [and not] يَنسَى [forgets]
data.transliteration: Qala AAilmuha AAinda rabbeefee kitabin la yadillu rabbee walayansa

data.textUthmani: ٱلَّذِى جَعَلَ لَكُمُ ٱلْأَرْضَ مَهْدًا وَسَلَكَ لَكُمْ فِيهَا سُبُلًا وَأَنزَلَ مِنَ ٱلسَّمَآءِ مَآءً فَأَخْرَجْنَا بِهِۦٓ أَزْوَٰجًا مِّن نَّبَاتٍ شَتَّىٰ
data.wordByWord: ٱلَّذِى [The One Who] جَعَلَ [made] لَكُمُ [for you] ٱلْأَرْضَ [the earth] مَهْدًۭا [(as) a bed] وَسَلَكَ [and inserted] لَكُمْ [for you] فِيهَا [therein] سُبُلًۭا [ways] وَأَنزَلَ [and sent down] مِنَ [from] ٱلسَّمَآءِ [the sky] مَآءًۭ [water] فَأَخْرَجْنَا [then We (have) brought forth] بِهِۦٓ [with it] أَزْوَٰجًۭا [pairs] مِّن [of] نَّبَاتٍۢ [plants] شَتَّىٰ [diverse]
data.transliteration: Allathee jaAAala lakumu al-ardamahdan wasalaka lakum feeha subulan waanzala mina assama-imaan faakhrajna bihi azwajan min nabatinshatta

data.textUthmani: كُلُوا۟ وَٱرْعَوْا۟ أَنْعَـٰمَكُمْ ۗ إِنَّ فِى ذَٰلِكَ لَـَٔايَـٰتٍ لِّأُو۟لِى ٱلنُّهَىٰ
data.wordByWord: كُلُوا۟ [Eat] وَٱرْعَوْا۟ [and pasture] أَنْعَـٰمَكُمْ ۗ [your cattle] إِنَّ [Indeed] فِى [in] ذَٰلِكَ [that] لَـَٔايَـٰتٍۢ [surely (are) Signs] لِّأُو۟لِى [for possessors] ٱلنُّهَىٰ [(of) intelligence]
data.transliteration: Kuloo warAAaw anAAamakum innafee thalika laayatin li-olee annuha

data.textUthmani: ۞ مِنْهَا خَلَقْنَـٰكُمْ وَفِيهَا نُعِيدُكُمْ وَمِنْهَا نُخْرِجُكُمْ تَارَةً أُخْرَىٰ
data.wordByWord: ۞ مِنْهَا [From it] خَلَقْنَـٰكُمْ [We created you] وَفِيهَا [and in it] نُعِيدُكُمْ [We will return you] وَمِنْهَا [and from it] نُخْرِجُكُمْ [We will bring you out] تَارَةً [time] أُخْرَىٰ [another]
data.transliteration: Minha khalaqnakum wafeehanuAAeedukum waminha nukhrijukum taratan okhra

data.textUthmani: وَلَقَدْ أَرَيْنَـٰهُ ءَايَـٰتِنَا كُلَّهَا فَكَذَّبَ وَأَبَىٰ
data.wordByWord: وَلَقَدْ [And verily] أَرَيْنَـٰهُ [We showed him] ءَايَـٰتِنَا [Our Signs] كُلَّهَا [all of them] فَكَذَّبَ [but he denied] وَأَبَىٰ [and refused]
data.transliteration: Walaqad araynahu ayatinakullaha fakaththaba waaba

data.textUthmani: قَالَ أَجِئْتَنَا لِتُخْرِجَنَا مِنْ أَرْضِنَا بِسِحْرِكَ يَـٰمُوسَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] أَجِئْتَنَا [Have you come to us] لِتُخْرِجَنَا [to drive us out] مِنْ [of] أَرْضِنَا [our land] بِسِحْرِكَ [with your magic] يَـٰمُوسَىٰ [O Musa]
data.transliteration: Qala aji/tana litukhrijanamin ardina bisihrika ya moosa

data.textUthmani: فَلَنَأْتِيَنَّكَ بِسِحْرٍ مِّثْلِهِۦ فَٱجْعَلْ بَيْنَنَا وَبَيْنَكَ مَوْعِدًا لَّا نُخْلِفُهُۥ نَحْنُ وَلَآ أَنتَ مَكَانًا سُوًى
data.wordByWord: فَلَنَأْتِيَنَّكَ [Then we will surely produce for you] بِسِحْرٍۢ [magic] مِّثْلِهِۦ [like it] فَٱجْعَلْ [So make] بَيْنَنَا [between us] وَبَيْنَكَ [and between you] مَوْعِدًۭا [an appointment] لَّا [not] نُخْلِفُهُۥ [we will fail it] نَحْنُ [[we]] وَلَآ [and not] أَنتَ [you] مَكَانًۭا [(in) a place] سُوًۭى [even]
data.transliteration: Falana/tiyannaka bisihrin mithlihi fajAAalbaynana wabaynaka mawAAidan la nukhlifuhu nahnuwala anta makanan suwa

words.translation: Then we will surely produce for you

data.textUthmani: قَالَ مَوْعِدُكُمْ يَوْمُ ٱلزِّينَةِ وَأَن يُحْشَرَ ٱلنَّاسُ ضُحًى
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] مَوْعِدُكُمْ [Your appointment] يَوْمُ [(is on the) day] ٱلزِّينَةِ [(of) the festival] وَأَن [and that] يُحْشَرَ [will be assembled] ٱلنَّاسُ [the people] ضُحًۭى [(at) forenoon]
data.transliteration: Qala mawAAidukum yawmu azzeenatiwaan yuhshara annasu duha

data.textUthmani: فَتَوَلَّىٰ فِرْعَوْنُ فَجَمَعَ كَيْدَهُۥ ثُمَّ أَتَىٰ
data.wordByWord: فَتَوَلَّىٰ [Then went away] فِرْعَوْنُ [Firaun] فَجَمَعَ [and put together] كَيْدَهُۥ [his plan] ثُمَّ [then] أَتَىٰ [came]
data.transliteration: Fatawalla firAAawnu fajamaAAa kaydahuthumma ata

data.textUthmani: قَالَ لَهُم مُّوسَىٰ وَيْلَكُمْ لَا تَفْتَرُوا۟ عَلَى ٱللَّهِ كَذِبًا فَيُسْحِتَكُم بِعَذَابٍ ۖ وَقَدْ خَابَ مَنِ ٱفْتَرَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [Said] لَهُم [to them] مُّوسَىٰ [Musa] وَيْلَكُمْ [Woe to you] لَا [(Do) not] تَفْتَرُوا۟ [invent] عَلَى [against] ٱللَّهِ [Allah] كَذِبًۭا [a lie] فَيُسْحِتَكُم [lest He will destroy you] بِعَذَابٍۢ ۖ [with a punishment] وَقَدْ [And verily] خَابَ [he failed] مَنِ [who] ٱفْتَرَىٰ [invented]
data.transliteration: Qala lahum moosa waylakum lataftaroo AAala Allahi kathiban fayushitakumbiAAathabin waqad khaba mani iftara

data.textUthmani: فَتَنَـٰزَعُوٓا۟ أَمْرَهُم بَيْنَهُمْ وَأَسَرُّوا۟ ٱلنَّجْوَىٰ
data.wordByWord: فَتَنَـٰزَعُوٓا۟ [Then they disputed] أَمْرَهُم [(in) their affair] بَيْنَهُمْ [among them] وَأَسَرُّوا۟ [and they kept secret] ٱلنَّجْوَىٰ [the private conversation]
data.transliteration: FatanazaAAoo amrahum baynahumwaasarroo annajwa

data.textUthmani: قَالُوٓا۟ إِنْ هَـٰذَٰنِ لَسَـٰحِرَٰنِ يُرِيدَانِ أَن يُخْرِجَاكُم مِّنْ أَرْضِكُم بِسِحْرِهِمَا وَيَذْهَبَا بِطَرِيقَتِكُمُ ٱلْمُثْلَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالُوٓا۟ [They said] إِنْ [Indeed] هَـٰذَٰنِ [these two] لَسَـٰحِرَٰنِ [[two] magicians] يُرِيدَانِ [they intend] أَن [that] يُخْرِجَاكُم [they drive you out] مِّنْ [of] أَرْضِكُم [your land] بِسِحْرِهِمَا [with their magic] وَيَذْهَبَا [and do away] بِطَرِيقَتِكُمُ [with your way] ٱلْمُثْلَىٰ [the exemplary]
data.transliteration: Qaloo in hathani lasahiraniyureedani an yukhrijakum min ardikum bisihrihimawayathhaba bitareeqatikumu almuthla

data.textUthmani: فَأَجْمِعُوا۟ كَيْدَكُمْ ثُمَّ ٱئْتُوا۟ صَفًّا ۚ وَقَدْ أَفْلَحَ ٱلْيَوْمَ مَنِ ٱسْتَعْلَىٰ
data.wordByWord: فَأَجْمِعُوا۟ [So put together] كَيْدَكُمْ [your plan] ثُمَّ [then] ٱئْتُوا۟ [come] صَفًّۭا ۚ [(in) a line] وَقَدْ [And verily] أَفْلَحَ [(will be) successful] ٱلْيَوْمَ [today] مَنِ [who] ٱسْتَعْلَىٰ [overcomes]
data.transliteration: FaajmiAAoo kaydakum thumma i/too saffanwaqad aflaha alyawma mani istaAAla

data.textUthmani: قَالُوا۟ يَـٰمُوسَىٰٓ إِمَّآ أَن تُلْقِىَ وَإِمَّآ أَن نَّكُونَ أَوَّلَ مَنْ أَلْقَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالُوا۟ [They said] يَـٰمُوسَىٰٓ [O Musa] إِمَّآ [Either] أَن [[that]] تُلْقِىَ [you throw] وَإِمَّآ [or] أَن [[that]] نَّكُونَ [we will be] أَوَّلَ [the first] مَنْ [who] أَلْقَىٰ [throws]
data.transliteration: Qaloo ya moosa immaan tulqiya wa-imma an nakoona awwala man alqa

data.textUthmani: قَالَ بَلْ أَلْقُوا۟ ۖ فَإِذَا حِبَالُهُمْ وَعِصِيُّهُمْ يُخَيَّلُ إِلَيْهِ مِن سِحْرِهِمْ أَنَّهَا تَسْعَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] بَلْ [Nay] أَلْقُوا۟ ۖ [you throw] فَإِذَا [Then behold] حِبَالُهُمْ [Their ropes] وَعِصِيُّهُمْ [and their staffs] يُخَيَّلُ [seemed] إِلَيْهِ [to him] مِن [by] سِحْرِهِمْ [their magic] أَنَّهَا [that they] تَسْعَىٰ [(were) moving]
data.transliteration: Qala bal alqoo fa-itha hibaluhumwaAAisiyyuhum yukhayyalu ilayhi min sihrihim annahatasAAa

data.textUthmani: فَأَوْجَسَ فِى نَفْسِهِۦ خِيفَةً مُّوسَىٰ
data.wordByWord: فَأَوْجَسَ [So sensed] فِى [in] نَفْسِهِۦ [himself] خِيفَةًۭ [a fear] مُّوسَىٰ [Musa]
data.transliteration: Faawjasa fee nafsihi kheefatan moosa

data.textUthmani: قُلْنَا لَا تَخَفْ إِنَّكَ أَنتَ ٱلْأَعْلَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قُلْنَا [We said] لَا [(Do) not] تَخَفْ [fear] إِنَّكَ [Indeed, you] أَنتَ [you] ٱلْأَعْلَىٰ [(will be) superior]
data.transliteration: Qulna la takhaf innaka antaal-aAAla

data.textUthmani: وَأَلْقِ مَا فِى يَمِينِكَ تَلْقَفْ مَا صَنَعُوٓا۟ ۖ إِنَّمَا صَنَعُوا۟ كَيْدُ سَـٰحِرٍ ۖ وَلَا يُفْلِحُ ٱلسَّاحِرُ حَيْثُ أَتَىٰ
data.wordByWord: وَأَلْقِ [And throw] مَا [what] فِى [(is) in] يَمِينِكَ [your right hand] تَلْقَفْ [it will swallow up] مَا [what] صَنَعُوٓا۟ ۖ [they have made] إِنَّمَا [Only] صَنَعُوا۟ [they (have) made] كَيْدُ [a trick] سَـٰحِرٍۢ ۖ [(of) a magician] وَلَا [and not] يُفْلِحُ [will be successful] ٱلسَّاحِرُ [the magician] حَيْثُ [wherever] أَتَىٰ [he comes]
data.transliteration: Waalqi ma fee yameenika talqaf masanaAAoo innama sanaAAoo kaydu sahirinwala yuflihu assahiru haythuata

data.textUthmani: فَأُلْقِىَ ٱلسَّحَرَةُ سُجَّدًا قَالُوٓا۟ ءَامَنَّا بِرَبِّ هَـٰرُونَ وَمُوسَىٰ
data.wordByWord: فَأُلْقِىَ [So were thrown down] ٱلسَّحَرَةُ [the magicians] سُجَّدًۭا [prostrating] قَالُوٓا۟ [They said] ءَامَنَّا [We believe] بِرَبِّ [in (the) Lord] هَـٰرُونَ [(of) Harun] وَمُوسَىٰ [and Musa]
data.transliteration: Faolqiya assaharatu sujjadanqaloo amanna birabbi haroona wamoosa

data.textUthmani: قَالَ ءَامَنتُمْ لَهُۥ قَبْلَ أَنْ ءَاذَنَ لَكُمْ ۖ إِنَّهُۥ لَكَبِيرُكُمُ ٱلَّذِى عَلَّمَكُمُ ٱلسِّحْرَ ۖ فَلَأُقَطِّعَنَّ أَيْدِيَكُمْ وَأَرْجُلَكُم مِّنْ خِلَـٰفٍ وَلَأُصَلِّبَنَّكُمْ فِى جُذُوعِ ٱلنَّخْلِ وَلَتَعْلَمُنَّ أَيُّنَآ أَشَدُّ عَذَابًا وَأَبْقَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] ءَامَنتُمْ [You believe] لَهُۥ [[to] him] قَبْلَ [before] أَنْ [[that]] ءَاذَنَ [I gave permission] لَكُمْ ۖ [to you] إِنَّهُۥ [Indeed, he] لَكَبِيرُكُمُ [(is) your chief] ٱلَّذِى [the one who] عَلَّمَكُمُ [taught you] ٱلسِّحْرَ ۖ [the magic] فَلَأُقَطِّعَنَّ [So surely I will cut off] أَيْدِيَكُمْ [your hands] وَأَرْجُلَكُم [and your feet] مِّنْ [of] خِلَـٰفٍۢ [opposite sides] وَلَأُصَلِّبَنَّكُمْ [and surely I will crucify you] فِى [on] جُذُوعِ [(the) trunks] ٱلنَّخْلِ [(of) date-palms] وَلَتَعْلَمُنَّ [and surely you will know] أَيُّنَآ [which of us] أَشَدُّ [(is) more severe] عَذَابًۭا [(in) punishment] وَأَبْقَىٰ [and more lasting]
data.transliteration: Qala amantum lahu qabla an athanalakum innahu lakabeerukumu allathee AAallamakumu assihrafalaoqattiAAanna aydiyakum waarjulakum min khilafinwalaosallibannakum fee juthooAAi annakhliwalataAAlamunna ayyuna ashaddu AAathaban waabqa

words.translation: So surely I will cut off
and surely I will crucify you

data.textUthmani: قَالُوا۟ لَن نُّؤْثِرَكَ عَلَىٰ مَا جَآءَنَا مِنَ ٱلْبَيِّنَـٰتِ وَٱلَّذِى فَطَرَنَا ۖ فَٱقْضِ مَآ أَنتَ قَاضٍ ۖ إِنَّمَا تَقْضِى هَـٰذِهِ ٱلْحَيَوٰةَ ٱلدُّنْيَآ
data.wordByWord: قَالُوا۟ [They said] لَن [Never] نُّؤْثِرَكَ [we will prefer you] عَلَىٰ [over] مَا [what] جَآءَنَا [has come to us] مِنَ [of] ٱلْبَيِّنَـٰتِ [the clear proofs] وَٱلَّذِى [and the One Who] فَطَرَنَا ۖ [created us] فَٱقْضِ [So decree] مَآ [whatever] أَنتَ [you] قَاضٍ ۖ [(are) decreeing] إِنَّمَا [Only] تَقْضِى [you can decree] هَـٰذِهِ [(for) this] ٱلْحَيَوٰةَ [life] ٱلدُّنْيَآ [(of) the world]
data.transliteration: Qaloo lan nu/thiraka AAala majaana mina albayyinati wallatheefatarana faqdi ma anta qadininnama taqdee hathihi alhayataaddunya

data.textUthmani: إِنَّآ ءَامَنَّا بِرَبِّنَا لِيَغْفِرَ لَنَا خَطَـٰيَـٰنَا وَمَآ أَكْرَهْتَنَا عَلَيْهِ مِنَ ٱلسِّحْرِ ۗ وَٱللَّهُ خَيْرٌ وَأَبْقَىٰٓ
data.wordByWord: إِنَّآ [Indeed, [we]] ءَامَنَّا [we believe] بِرَبِّنَا [in our Lord] لِيَغْفِرَ [that He may forgive] لَنَا [for us] خَطَـٰيَـٰنَا [our sins] وَمَآ [and what] أَكْرَهْتَنَا [you compelled us] عَلَيْهِ [on it] مِنَ [of] ٱلسِّحْرِ ۗ [the magic] وَٱللَّهُ [And Allah] خَيْرٌۭ [(is) Best] وَأَبْقَىٰٓ [and Ever Lasting]
data.transliteration: Inna amanna birabbinaliyaghfira lana khatayana wamaakrahtana AAalayhi mina assihri wallahukhayrun waabqa

data.textUthmani: إِنَّهُۥ مَن يَأْتِ رَبَّهُۥ مُجْرِمًا فَإِنَّ لَهُۥ جَهَنَّمَ لَا يَمُوتُ فِيهَا وَلَا يَحْيَىٰ
data.wordByWord: إِنَّهُۥ [Indeed, he] مَن [who] يَأْتِ [comes] رَبَّهُۥ [(to) his Lord] مُجْرِمًۭا [(as) a criminal] فَإِنَّ [then indeed] لَهُۥ [for him] جَهَنَّمَ [(is) Hell] لَا [Not] يَمُوتُ [he will die] فِيهَا [in it] وَلَا [and not] يَحْيَىٰ [live]
data.transliteration: Innahu man ya/ti rabbahu mujriman fa-innalahu jahannama la yamootu feeha wala yahya

data.textUthmani: وَمَن يَأْتِهِۦ مُؤْمِنًا قَدْ عَمِلَ ٱلصَّـٰلِحَـٰتِ فَأُو۟لَـٰٓئِكَ لَهُمُ ٱلدَّرَجَـٰتُ ٱلْعُلَىٰ
data.wordByWord: وَمَن [But whoever] يَأْتِهِۦ [comes to Him] مُؤْمِنًۭا [(as) a believer] قَدْ [verily] عَمِلَ [he has done] ٱلصَّـٰلِحَـٰتِ [the righteous deeds] فَأُو۟لَـٰٓئِكَ [then those] لَهُمُ [for them] ٱلدَّرَجَـٰتُ [(will be) the ranks] ٱلْعُلَىٰ [[the] high]
data.transliteration: Waman ya/tihi mu/minan qad AAamila assalihatifaola-ika lahumu addarajatu alAAula

data.textUthmani: جَنَّـٰتُ عَدْنٍ تَجْرِى مِن تَحْتِهَا ٱلْأَنْهَـٰرُ خَـٰلِدِينَ فِيهَا ۚ وَذَٰلِكَ جَزَآءُ مَن تَزَكَّىٰ
data.wordByWord: جَنَّـٰتُ [Gardens] عَدْنٍۢ [(of) Eden] تَجْرِى [flows] مِن [from] تَحْتِهَا [underneath them] ٱلْأَنْهَـٰرُ [the rivers] خَـٰلِدِينَ [abiding forever] فِيهَا ۚ [in it] وَذَٰلِكَ [And that] جَزَآءُ [(is) the reward] مَن [(for him) who] تَزَكَّىٰ [purifies himself]
data.transliteration: Jannatu AAadnin tajree min tahtihaal-anharu khalideena feeha wathalikajazao man tazakka

data.textUthmani: وَلَقَدْ أَوْحَيْنَآ إِلَىٰ مُوسَىٰٓ أَنْ أَسْرِ بِعِبَادِى فَٱضْرِبْ لَهُمْ طَرِيقًا فِى ٱلْبَحْرِ يَبَسًا لَّا تَخَـٰفُ دَرَكًا وَلَا تَخْشَىٰ
data.wordByWord: وَلَقَدْ [And verily] أَوْحَيْنَآ [We inspired] إِلَىٰ [to] مُوسَىٰٓ [Musa] أَنْ [that] أَسْرِ [Travel by night] بِعِبَادِى [with My slaves] فَٱضْرِبْ [and strike] لَهُمْ [for them] طَرِيقًۭا [a path] فِى [in] ٱلْبَحْرِ [the sea] يَبَسًۭا [dry] لَّا [not] تَخَـٰفُ [fearing] دَرَكًۭا [to be overtaken] وَلَا [and not] تَخْشَىٰ [being afraid]
data.transliteration: Walaqad awhayna ilamoosa an asri biAAibadee fadriblahum tareeqan fee albahri yabasan la takhafudarakan wala takhsha

data.textUthmani: فَأَتْبَعَهُمْ فِرْعَوْنُ بِجُنُودِهِۦ فَغَشِيَهُم مِّنَ ٱلْيَمِّ مَا غَشِيَهُمْ
data.wordByWord: فَأَتْبَعَهُمْ [Then followed them] فِرْعَوْنُ [Firaun] بِجُنُودِهِۦ [with his forces] فَغَشِيَهُم [but covered them] مِّنَ [from] ٱلْيَمِّ [the sea] مَا [what] غَشِيَهُمْ [covered them]
data.transliteration: FaatbaAAahum firAAawnu bijunoodihifaghashiyahum mina alyammi ma ghashiyahum

data.textUthmani: وَأَضَلَّ فِرْعَوْنُ قَوْمَهُۥ وَمَا هَدَىٰ
data.wordByWord: وَأَضَلَّ [And led astray] فِرْعَوْنُ [Firaun] قَوْمَهُۥ [his people] وَمَا [and (did) not] هَدَىٰ [guide them]
data.transliteration: Waadalla firAAawnu qawmahu wamahada

data.textUthmani: يَـٰبَنِىٓ إِسْرَٰٓءِيلَ قَدْ أَنجَيْنَـٰكُم مِّنْ عَدُوِّكُمْ وَوَٰعَدْنَـٰكُمْ جَانِبَ ٱلطُّورِ ٱلْأَيْمَنَ وَنَزَّلْنَا عَلَيْكُمُ ٱلْمَنَّ وَٱلسَّلْوَىٰ
data.wordByWord: يَـٰبَنِىٓ [O Children of Israel] إِسْرَٰٓءِيلَ [O Children of Israel] قَدْ [Verily] أَنجَيْنَـٰكُم [We delivered you] مِّنْ [from] عَدُوِّكُمْ [your enemy] وَوَٰعَدْنَـٰكُمْ [and We made a covenant with you] جَانِبَ [on (the) side] ٱلطُّورِ [(of) the Mount] ٱلْأَيْمَنَ [the right] وَنَزَّلْنَا [and We sent down] عَلَيْكُمُ [to you] ٱلْمَنَّ [the Manna] وَٱلسَّلْوَىٰ [and the quails]
data.transliteration: Ya banee isra-eela qad anjaynakummin AAaduwwikum wawaAAadnakum janiba attoorial-aymana wanazzalna AAalaykumu almanna wassalwa

words.translation: and We made a covenant with you

data.textUthmani: كُلُوا۟ مِن طَيِّبَـٰتِ مَا رَزَقْنَـٰكُمْ وَلَا تَطْغَوْا۟ فِيهِ فَيَحِلَّ عَلَيْكُمْ غَضَبِى ۖ وَمَن يَحْلِلْ عَلَيْهِ غَضَبِى فَقَدْ هَوَىٰ
data.wordByWord: كُلُوا۟ [Eat] مِن [of] طَيِّبَـٰتِ [(the) good things] مَا [which] رَزَقْنَـٰكُمْ [We have provided you] وَلَا [and (do) not] تَطْغَوْا۟ [transgress] فِيهِ [therein] فَيَحِلَّ [lest should descend] عَلَيْكُمْ [upon you] غَضَبِى ۖ [My Anger] وَمَن [And whoever] يَحْلِلْ [on whom descends] عَلَيْهِ [on whom descends] غَضَبِى [My Anger] فَقَدْ [indeed] هَوَىٰ [he (has) perished]
data.transliteration: Kuloo min tayyibati marazaqnakum wala tatghaw feehi fayahillaAAalaykum ghadabee waman yahlil AAalayhi ghadabeefaqad hawa

data.textUthmani: وَإِنِّى لَغَفَّارٌ لِّمَن تَابَ وَءَامَنَ وَعَمِلَ صَـٰلِحًا ثُمَّ ٱهْتَدَىٰ
data.wordByWord: وَإِنِّى [But indeed, I Am] لَغَفَّارٌۭ [the Perpetual Forgiver] لِّمَن [of whoever] تَابَ [repents] وَءَامَنَ [and believes] وَعَمِلَ [and does] صَـٰلِحًۭا [righteous (deeds)] ثُمَّ [then] ٱهْتَدَىٰ [remains guided]
data.transliteration: Wa-innee laghaffarun liman tabawaamana waAAamila salihan thumma ihtada

data.textUthmani: ۞ وَمَآ أَعْجَلَكَ عَن قَوْمِكَ يَـٰمُوسَىٰ
data.wordByWord: ۞ وَمَآ [And what] أَعْجَلَكَ [made you hasten] عَن [from] قَوْمِكَ [your people] يَـٰمُوسَىٰ [O Musa]
data.transliteration: Wama aAAjalaka AAan qawmika yamoosa

data.textUthmani: قَالَ هُمْ أُو۟لَآءِ عَلَىٰٓ أَثَرِى وَعَجِلْتُ إِلَيْكَ رَبِّ لِتَرْضَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] هُمْ [They] أُو۟لَآءِ [(are) close] عَلَىٰٓ [upon] أَثَرِى [my tracks] وَعَجِلْتُ [and I hastened] إِلَيْكَ [to you] رَبِّ [my Lord] لِتَرْضَىٰ [that You be pleased]
data.transliteration: Qala hum ola-i AAalaatharee waAAajiltu ilayka rabbi litarda

data.textUthmani: قَالَ فَإِنَّا قَدْ فَتَنَّا قَوْمَكَ مِنۢ بَعْدِكَ وَأَضَلَّهُمُ ٱلسَّامِرِىُّ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] فَإِنَّا [But indeed, We] قَدْ [[verily]] فَتَنَّا [We (have) tried] قَوْمَكَ [your people] مِنۢ [after you] بَعْدِكَ [after you] وَأَضَلَّهُمُ [and has led them astray] ٱلسَّامِرِىُّ [the Samiri]
data.transliteration: Qala fa-inna qad fatannaqawmaka min baAAdika waadallahumu assamiriy

data.textUthmani: فَرَجَعَ مُوسَىٰٓ إِلَىٰ قَوْمِهِۦ غَضْبَـٰنَ أَسِفًا ۚ قَالَ يَـٰقَوْمِ أَلَمْ يَعِدْكُمْ رَبُّكُمْ وَعْدًا حَسَنًا ۚ أَفَطَالَ عَلَيْكُمُ ٱلْعَهْدُ أَمْ أَرَدتُّمْ أَن يَحِلَّ عَلَيْكُمْ غَضَبٌ مِّن رَّبِّكُمْ فَأَخْلَفْتُم مَّوْعِدِى
data.wordByWord: فَرَجَعَ [Then Musa returned] مُوسَىٰٓ [Then Musa returned] إِلَىٰ [to] قَوْمِهِۦ [his people] غَضْبَـٰنَ [angry] أَسِفًۭا ۚ [(and) sorrowful] قَالَ [He said] يَـٰقَوْمِ [O my people] أَلَمْ [Did not] يَعِدْكُمْ [promise you] رَبُّكُمْ [your Lord] وَعْدًا [a promise] حَسَنًا ۚ [good] أَفَطَالَ [Then, did seem long] عَلَيْكُمُ [to you] ٱلْعَهْدُ [the promise] أَمْ [or] أَرَدتُّمْ [did you desire] أَن [that] يَحِلَّ [descend] عَلَيْكُمْ [upon you] غَضَبٌۭ [(the) Anger] مِّن [of] رَّبِّكُمْ [your Lord] فَأَخْلَفْتُم [so you broke] مَّوْعِدِى [(the) promise to me]
data.transliteration: FarajaAAa moosa ila qawmihighadbana asifan qala ya qawmi alamyaAAidkum rabbukum waAAdan hasanan afatalaAAalaykumu alAAahdu am aradtum an yahilla AAalaykum ghadabunmin rabbikum faakhlaftum mawAAidee

data.textUthmani: قَالُوا۟ مَآ أَخْلَفْنَا مَوْعِدَكَ بِمَلْكِنَا وَلَـٰكِنَّا حُمِّلْنَآ أَوْزَارًا مِّن زِينَةِ ٱلْقَوْمِ فَقَذَفْنَـٰهَا فَكَذَٰلِكَ أَلْقَى ٱلسَّامِرِىُّ
data.wordByWord: قَالُوا۟ [They said] مَآ [Not] أَخْلَفْنَا [we broke] مَوْعِدَكَ [promise to you] بِمَلْكِنَا [by our will] وَلَـٰكِنَّا [but we] حُمِّلْنَآ [[we] were made to carry] أَوْزَارًۭا [burdens] مِّن [from] زِينَةِ [ornaments] ٱلْقَوْمِ [(of) the people] فَقَذَفْنَـٰهَا [so we threw them] فَكَذَٰلِكَ [and thus] أَلْقَى [threw] ٱلسَّامِرِىُّ [the Samiri]
data.transliteration: Qaloo ma akhlafnamawAAidaka bimalkina walakinna hummilnaawzaran min zeenati alqawmi faqathafnahafakathalika alqa assamiriy

data.textUthmani: فَأَخْرَجَ لَهُمْ عِجْلًا جَسَدًا لَّهُۥ خُوَارٌ فَقَالُوا۟ هَـٰذَآ إِلَـٰهُكُمْ وَإِلَـٰهُ مُوسَىٰ فَنَسِىَ
data.wordByWord: فَأَخْرَجَ [Then he brought forth] لَهُمْ [for them] عِجْلًۭا [a calf's] جَسَدًۭا [body] لَّهُۥ [it had] خُوَارٌۭ [a lowing sound] فَقَالُوا۟ [and they said] هَـٰذَآ [This] إِلَـٰهُكُمْ [(is) your god] وَإِلَـٰهُ [and the god] مُوسَىٰ [(of) Musa] فَنَسِىَ [but he forgot]
data.transliteration: Faakhraja lahum AAijlan jasadan lahu khuwarunfaqaloo hatha ilahukum wa-ilahu moosafanasiy

data.textUthmani: أَفَلَا يَرَوْنَ أَلَّا يَرْجِعُ إِلَيْهِمْ قَوْلًا وَلَا يَمْلِكُ لَهُمْ ضَرًّا وَلَا نَفْعًا
data.wordByWord: أَفَلَا [Then, did not] يَرَوْنَ [they see] أَلَّا [that not] يَرْجِعُ [it (could) return] إِلَيْهِمْ [to them] قَوْلًۭا [a word] وَلَا [and not] يَمْلِكُ [possess] لَهُمْ [for them] ضَرًّۭا [any harm] وَلَا [and not] نَفْعًۭا [any benefit]
data.transliteration: Afala yarawna alla yarjiAAuilayhim qawlan wala yamliku lahum darran walanafAAa

data.textUthmani: وَلَقَدْ قَالَ لَهُمْ هَـٰرُونُ مِن قَبْلُ يَـٰقَوْمِ إِنَّمَا فُتِنتُم بِهِۦ ۖ وَإِنَّ رَبَّكُمُ ٱلرَّحْمَـٰنُ فَٱتَّبِعُونِى وَأَطِيعُوٓا۟ أَمْرِى
data.wordByWord: وَلَقَدْ [And verily] قَالَ [(had) said] لَهُمْ [to them] هَـٰرُونُ [Harun] مِن [before] قَبْلُ [before] يَـٰقَوْمِ [O my people] إِنَّمَا [Only] فُتِنتُم [you are being tested] بِهِۦ ۖ [by it] وَإِنَّ [and indeed] رَبَّكُمُ [your Lord] ٱلرَّحْمَـٰنُ [(is) the Most Gracious] فَٱتَّبِعُونِى [so follow me] وَأَطِيعُوٓا۟ [and obey] أَمْرِى [my order]
data.transliteration: Walaqad qala lahum haroonu minqablu ya qawmi innama futintum bihi wa-innarabbakumu arrahmanu fattabiAAooneewaateeAAoo amree

data.textUthmani: قَالُوا۟ لَن نَّبْرَحَ عَلَيْهِ عَـٰكِفِينَ حَتَّىٰ يَرْجِعَ إِلَيْنَا مُوسَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالُوا۟ [They said] لَن [Never] نَّبْرَحَ [we will cease] عَلَيْهِ [being devoted to it] عَـٰكِفِينَ [being devoted to it] حَتَّىٰ [until] يَرْجِعَ [returns] إِلَيْنَا [to us] مُوسَىٰ [Musa]
data.transliteration: Qaloo lan nabraha AAalayhi AAakifeenahatta yarjiAAa ilayna moosa

data.textUthmani: قَالَ يَـٰهَـٰرُونُ مَا مَنَعَكَ إِذْ رَأَيْتَهُمْ ضَلُّوٓا۟
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] يَـٰهَـٰرُونُ [O Harun] مَا [What] مَنَعَكَ [prevented you] إِذْ [when] رَأَيْتَهُمْ [you saw them] ضَلُّوٓا۟ [going astray]
data.transliteration: Qala ya haroonu mamanaAAaka ith raaytahum dalloo

data.textUthmani: أَلَّا تَتَّبِعَنِ ۖ أَفَعَصَيْتَ أَمْرِى
data.wordByWord: أَلَّا [That not] تَتَّبِعَنِ ۖ [you follow me] أَفَعَصَيْتَ [Then, have you disobeyed] أَمْرِى [my order]
data.transliteration: Alla tattabiAAani afaAAasaytaamree

data.textUthmani: قَالَ يَبْنَؤُمَّ لَا تَأْخُذْ بِلِحْيَتِى وَلَا بِرَأْسِىٓ ۖ إِنِّى خَشِيتُ أَن تَقُولَ فَرَّقْتَ بَيْنَ بَنِىٓ إِسْرَٰٓءِيلَ وَلَمْ تَرْقُبْ قَوْلِى
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] يَبْنَؤُمَّ [O son of my mother] لَا [(Do) not] تَأْخُذْ [seize (me)] بِلِحْيَتِى [by my beard] وَلَا [and not] بِرَأْسِىٓ ۖ [by my head] إِنِّى [Indeed, I] خَشِيتُ [[I] feared] أَن [that] تَقُولَ [you would say] فَرَّقْتَ [You caused division] بَيْنَ [between] بَنِىٓ [(the) Children of Israel] إِسْرَٰٓءِيلَ [(the) Children of Israel] وَلَمْ [and not] تَرْقُبْ [you respect] قَوْلِى [my word]
data.transliteration: Qala yabnaomma la ta/khuthbilihyatee wala bira/see innee khasheetu an taqoolafarraqta bayna banee isra-eela walam tarqub qawlee

data.textUthmani: قَالَ فَمَا خَطْبُكَ يَـٰسَـٰمِرِىُّ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] فَمَا [Then what] خَطْبُكَ [(is) your case] يَـٰسَـٰمِرِىُّ [O Samiri]
data.transliteration: Qala fama khatbuka yasamiriy

data.textUthmani: قَالَ بَصُرْتُ بِمَا لَمْ يَبْصُرُوا۟ بِهِۦ فَقَبَضْتُ قَبْضَةً مِّنْ أَثَرِ ٱلرَّسُولِ فَنَبَذْتُهَا وَكَذَٰلِكَ سَوَّلَتْ لِى نَفْسِى
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] بَصُرْتُ [I perceived] بِمَا [what] لَمْ [not] يَبْصُرُوا۟ [they perceive] بِهِۦ [in it] فَقَبَضْتُ [so I took] قَبْضَةًۭ [a handful] مِّنْ [from] أَثَرِ [(the) track] ٱلرَّسُولِ [(of) the Messenger] فَنَبَذْتُهَا [then threw it] وَكَذَٰلِكَ [and thus] سَوَّلَتْ [suggested] لِى [to me] نَفْسِى [my soul]
data.transliteration: Qala basurtu bima lamyabsuroo bihi faqabadtu qabdatan min athariarrasooli fanabathtuha wakathalikasawwalat lee nafsee

data.textUthmani: قَالَ فَٱذْهَبْ فَإِنَّ لَكَ فِى ٱلْحَيَوٰةِ أَن تَقُولَ لَا مِسَاسَ ۖ وَإِنَّ لَكَ مَوْعِدًا لَّن تُخْلَفَهُۥ ۖ وَٱنظُرْ إِلَىٰٓ إِلَـٰهِكَ ٱلَّذِى ظَلْتَ عَلَيْهِ عَاكِفًا ۖ لَّنُحَرِّقَنَّهُۥ ثُمَّ لَنَنسِفَنَّهُۥ فِى ٱلْيَمِّ نَسْفًا
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] فَٱذْهَبْ [Then go] فَإِنَّ [And indeed] لَكَ [for you] فِى [in] ٱلْحَيَوٰةِ [the life] أَن [that] تَقُولَ [you will say] لَا [(Do) not] مِسَاسَ ۖ [touch] وَإِنَّ [And indeed] لَكَ [for you] مَوْعِدًۭا [(is) an appointment] لَّن [never] تُخْلَفَهُۥ ۖ [you will fail to (keep) it] وَٱنظُرْ [And look] إِلَىٰٓ [at] إِلَـٰهِكَ [your god] ٱلَّذِى [that which] ظَلْتَ [you have remained] عَلَيْهِ [to it] عَاكِفًۭا ۖ [devoted] لَّنُحَرِّقَنَّهُۥ [Surely we will burn it] ثُمَّ [then] لَنَنسِفَنَّهُۥ [certainly we will scatter it] فِى [in] ٱلْيَمِّ [the sea] نَسْفًا [(in) particles]
data.transliteration: Qala fathhab fa-innalaka fee alhayati an taqoola la misasawa-inna laka mawAAidan lan tukhlafahu wanthurila ilahika allathee thaltaAAalayhi AAakifan lanuharriqannahu thummalanansifannahu fee alyammi nasfa

data.textUthmani: إِنَّمَآ إِلَـٰهُكُمُ ٱللَّهُ ٱلَّذِى لَآ إِلَـٰهَ إِلَّا هُوَ ۚ وَسِعَ كُلَّ شَىْءٍ عِلْمًا
data.wordByWord: إِنَّمَآ [Only] إِلَـٰهُكُمُ [your God] ٱللَّهُ [(is) Allah] ٱلَّذِى [the One] لَآ [(there is) no] إِلَـٰهَ [god] إِلَّا [but] هُوَ ۚ [He] وَسِعَ [He has encompassed] كُلَّ [all] شَىْءٍ [things] عِلْمًۭا [(in) knowledge]
data.transliteration: Innama ilahukumu Allahuallathee la ilaha illa huwa wasiAAakulla shay-in AAilma

data.textUthmani: كَذَٰلِكَ نَقُصُّ عَلَيْكَ مِنْ أَنۢبَآءِ مَا قَدْ سَبَقَ ۚ وَقَدْ ءَاتَيْنَـٰكَ مِن لَّدُنَّا ذِكْرًا
data.wordByWord: كَذَٰلِكَ [Thus] نَقُصُّ [We relate] عَلَيْكَ [to you] مِنْ [from] أَنۢبَآءِ [(the) news] مَا [(of) what] قَدْ [has preceded] سَبَقَ ۚ [has preceded] وَقَدْ [And certainly] ءَاتَيْنَـٰكَ [We have given you] مِن [from] لَّدُنَّا [Us] ذِكْرًۭا [a Reminder]
data.transliteration: Kathalika naqussu AAalayka minanba-i ma qad sabaqa waqad ataynakamin ladunna thikra

data.textUthmani: مَّنْ أَعْرَضَ عَنْهُ فَإِنَّهُۥ يَحْمِلُ يَوْمَ ٱلْقِيَـٰمَةِ وِزْرًا
data.wordByWord: مَّنْ [Whoever] أَعْرَضَ [turns away] عَنْهُ [from it] فَإِنَّهُۥ [then indeed, he] يَحْمِلُ [will bear] يَوْمَ [(on the) Day] ٱلْقِيَـٰمَةِ [(of) Resurrection] وِزْرًا [a burden]
data.transliteration: Man aAArada AAanhu fa-innahu yahmiluyawma alqiyamati wizra

data.textUthmani: خَـٰلِدِينَ فِيهِ ۖ وَسَآءَ لَهُمْ يَوْمَ ٱلْقِيَـٰمَةِ حِمْلًا
data.wordByWord: خَـٰلِدِينَ [Abiding forever] فِيهِ ۖ [in it] وَسَآءَ [and evil] لَهُمْ [for them] يَوْمَ [(on the) Day] ٱلْقِيَـٰمَةِ [(of) the Resurrection] حِمْلًۭا [(as) a load]
data.transliteration: Khalideena feehi wasaa lahumyawma alqiyamati himla

data.textUthmani: يَوْمَ يُنفَخُ فِى ٱلصُّورِ ۚ وَنَحْشُرُ ٱلْمُجْرِمِينَ يَوْمَئِذٍ زُرْقًا
data.wordByWord: يَوْمَ [(The) Day] يُنفَخُ [will be blown] فِى [in] ٱلصُّورِ ۚ [the Trumpet] وَنَحْشُرُ [and We will gather] ٱلْمُجْرِمِينَ [the criminals] يَوْمَئِذٍۢ [that Day] زُرْقًۭا [blue-eyed]
data.transliteration: Yawma yunfakhu fee assooriwanahshuru almujrimeena yawma-ithin zurqa

data.textUthmani: يَتَخَـٰفَتُونَ بَيْنَهُمْ إِن لَّبِثْتُمْ إِلَّا عَشْرًا
data.wordByWord: يَتَخَـٰفَتُونَ [They are murmuring] بَيْنَهُمْ [among themselves] إِن [Not] لَّبِثْتُمْ [you remained] إِلَّا [except (for)] عَشْرًۭا [ten]
data.transliteration: Yatakhafatoona baynahum in labithtumilla AAashra

data.textUthmani: نَّحْنُ أَعْلَمُ بِمَا يَقُولُونَ إِذْ يَقُولُ أَمْثَلُهُمْ طَرِيقَةً إِن لَّبِثْتُمْ إِلَّا يَوْمًا
data.wordByWord: نَّحْنُ [We] أَعْلَمُ [know best] بِمَا [what] يَقُولُونَ [they will say] إِذْ [when] يَقُولُ [will say] أَمْثَلُهُمْ [(the) best of them] طَرِيقَةً [(in) conduct] إِن [Not] لَّبِثْتُمْ [you remained] إِلَّا [except (for)] يَوْمًۭا [a day]
data.transliteration: Nahnu aAAlamu bima yaqooloonaith yaqoolu amthaluhum tareeqatan in labithtum illayawma

data.textUthmani: وَيَسْـَٔلُونَكَ عَنِ ٱلْجِبَالِ فَقُلْ يَنسِفُهَا رَبِّى نَسْفًا
data.wordByWord: وَيَسْـَٔلُونَكَ [And they ask you] عَنِ [about] ٱلْجِبَالِ [the mountains] فَقُلْ [so say] يَنسِفُهَا [Will blast them] رَبِّى [my Lord] نَسْفًۭا [(into) particles]
data.transliteration: Wayas-aloonaka AAani aljibali faqulyansifuha rabbee nasfa

data.textUthmani: فَيَذَرُهَا قَاعًا صَفْصَفًا
data.wordByWord: فَيَذَرُهَا [Then He will leave it] قَاعًۭا [a level] صَفْصَفًۭا [plain]
data.transliteration: Fayatharuha qaAAan safsafa

data.textUthmani: لَّا تَرَىٰ فِيهَا عِوَجًا وَلَآ أَمْتًا
data.wordByWord: لَّا [Not] تَرَىٰ [you will see] فِيهَا [in it] عِوَجًۭا [any crookedness] وَلَآ [and not] أَمْتًۭا [any curve]
data.transliteration: La tara feeha AAiwajanwala amta

data.textUthmani: يَوْمَئِذٍ يَتَّبِعُونَ ٱلدَّاعِىَ لَا عِوَجَ لَهُۥ ۖ وَخَشَعَتِ ٱلْأَصْوَاتُ لِلرَّحْمَـٰنِ فَلَا تَسْمَعُ إِلَّا هَمْسًا
data.wordByWord: يَوْمَئِذٍۢ [On that Day] يَتَّبِعُونَ [they will follow] ٱلدَّاعِىَ [the caller] لَا [no] عِوَجَ [deviation] لَهُۥ ۖ [from it] وَخَشَعَتِ [And (will be) humbled] ٱلْأَصْوَاتُ [the voices] لِلرَّحْمَـٰنِ [for the Most Gracious] فَلَا [so not] تَسْمَعُ [you will hear] إِلَّا [except] هَمْسًۭا [a faint sound]
data.transliteration: Yawma-ithin yattabiAAoona addaAAiyala AAiwaja lahu wakhashaAAati al-aswatu lirrahmanifala tasmaAAu illa hamsa

data.textUthmani: يَوْمَئِذٍ لَّا تَنفَعُ ٱلشَّفَـٰعَةُ إِلَّا مَنْ أَذِنَ لَهُ ٱلرَّحْمَـٰنُ وَرَضِىَ لَهُۥ قَوْلًا
data.wordByWord: يَوْمَئِذٍۢ [(On) that Day] لَّا [not] تَنفَعُ [will benefit] ٱلشَّفَـٰعَةُ [the intercession] إِلَّا [except] مَنْ [(to) whom] أَذِنَ [has given permission] لَهُ [[to him]] ٱلرَّحْمَـٰنُ [the Most Gracious] وَرَضِىَ [and He has accepted] لَهُۥ [for him] قَوْلًۭا [a word]
data.transliteration: Yawma-ithin la tanfaAAu ashshafaAAatuilla man athina lahu arrahmanuwaradiya lahu qawla

data.textUthmani: يَعْلَمُ مَا بَيْنَ أَيْدِيهِمْ وَمَا خَلْفَهُمْ وَلَا يُحِيطُونَ بِهِۦ عِلْمًا
data.wordByWord: يَعْلَمُ [He knows] مَا [what] بَيْنَ [(is) before them] أَيْدِيهِمْ [(is) before them] وَمَا [and what] خَلْفَهُمْ [(is) behind them] وَلَا [while not] يُحِيطُونَ [they encompass] بِهِۦ [it] عِلْمًۭا [(in) knowledge]
data.transliteration: YaAAlamu ma bayna aydeehim wamakhalfahum wala yuheetoona bihi AAilma

data.textUthmani: ۞ وَعَنَتِ ٱلْوُجُوهُ لِلْحَىِّ ٱلْقَيُّومِ ۖ وَقَدْ خَابَ مَنْ حَمَلَ ظُلْمًا
data.wordByWord: ۞ وَعَنَتِ [And (will be) humbled] ٱلْوُجُوهُ [the faces] لِلْحَىِّ [before the Ever-Living] ٱلْقَيُّومِ ۖ [the Self-Subsisting] وَقَدْ [And verily] خَابَ [will have failed] مَنْ [(he) who] حَمَلَ [carried] ظُلْمًۭا [wrongdoing]
data.transliteration: WaAAanati alwujoohu lilhayyialqayyoomi waqad khaba man hamala thulma

data.textUthmani: وَمَن يَعْمَلْ مِنَ ٱلصَّـٰلِحَـٰتِ وَهُوَ مُؤْمِنٌ فَلَا يَخَافُ ظُلْمًا وَلَا هَضْمًا
data.wordByWord: وَمَن [But (he) who] يَعْمَلْ [does] مِنَ [of] ٱلصَّـٰلِحَـٰتِ [the righteous deeds] وَهُوَ [while he] مُؤْمِنٌۭ [(is) a believer] فَلَا [then not] يَخَافُ [he will fear] ظُلْمًۭا [injustice] وَلَا [and not] هَضْمًۭا [deprivation]
data.transliteration: Waman yaAAmal mina assalihatiwahuwa mu/minun fala yakhafu thulmanwala hadma

data.textUthmani: وَكَذَٰلِكَ أَنزَلْنَـٰهُ قُرْءَانًا عَرَبِيًّا وَصَرَّفْنَا فِيهِ مِنَ ٱلْوَعِيدِ لَعَلَّهُمْ يَتَّقُونَ أَوْ يُحْدِثُ لَهُمْ ذِكْرًا
data.wordByWord: وَكَذَٰلِكَ [And thus] أَنزَلْنَـٰهُ [We have sent it down] قُرْءَانًا [(the) Quran] عَرَبِيًّۭا [(in) Arabic] وَصَرَّفْنَا [and We have explained] فِيهِ [in it] مِنَ [of] ٱلْوَعِيدِ [the warnings] لَعَلَّهُمْ [that they may] يَتَّقُونَ [fear] أَوْ [or] يُحْدِثُ [it may cause] لَهُمْ [[for] them] ذِكْرًۭا [remembrance]
data.transliteration: Wakathalika anzalnahu qur-ananAAarabiyyan wasarrafna feehi mina alwaAAeedilaAAallahum yattaqoona aw yuhdithu lahum thikra

data.textUthmani: فَتَعَـٰلَى ٱللَّهُ ٱلْمَلِكُ ٱلْحَقُّ ۗ وَلَا تَعْجَلْ بِٱلْقُرْءَانِ مِن قَبْلِ أَن يُقْضَىٰٓ إِلَيْكَ وَحْيُهُۥ ۖ وَقُل رَّبِّ زِدْنِى عِلْمًا
data.wordByWord: فَتَعَـٰلَى [So high (above all)] ٱللَّهُ [(is) Allah] ٱلْمَلِكُ [the King] ٱلْحَقُّ ۗ [the True] وَلَا [And (do) not] تَعْجَلْ [hasten] بِٱلْقُرْءَانِ [with the Quran] مِن [before] قَبْلِ [before] أَن [[that]] يُقْضَىٰٓ [is completed] إِلَيْكَ [to you] وَحْيُهُۥ ۖ [its revelation] وَقُل [and say] رَّبِّ [My Lord] زِدْنِى [Increase me] عِلْمًۭا [(in) knowledge]
data.transliteration: FataAAala Allahualmaliku alhaqqu wala taAAjal bilqur-animin qabli an yuqda ilayka wahyuhu waqul rabbizidnee AAilma

data.textUthmani: وَلَقَدْ عَهِدْنَآ إِلَىٰٓ ءَادَمَ مِن قَبْلُ فَنَسِىَ وَلَمْ نَجِدْ لَهُۥ عَزْمًا
data.wordByWord: وَلَقَدْ [And verily] عَهِدْنَآ [We made a covenant] إِلَىٰٓ [with] ءَادَمَ [Adam] مِن [before] قَبْلُ [before] فَنَسِىَ [but he forgot] وَلَمْ [and not] نَجِدْ [We found] لَهُۥ [in him] عَزْمًۭا [determination]
data.transliteration: Walaqad AAahidna ila adamamin qablu fanasiya walam najid lahu AAazma

data.textUthmani: وَإِذْ قُلْنَا لِلْمَلَـٰٓئِكَةِ ٱسْجُدُوا۟ لِـَٔادَمَ فَسَجَدُوٓا۟ إِلَّآ إِبْلِيسَ أَبَىٰ
data.wordByWord: وَإِذْ [And when] قُلْنَا [We said] لِلْمَلَـٰٓئِكَةِ [to the Angels] ٱسْجُدُوا۟ [Prostrate] لِـَٔادَمَ [to Adam] فَسَجَدُوٓا۟ [then they prostrated] إِلَّآ [except] إِبْلِيسَ [Iblis] أَبَىٰ [he refused]
data.transliteration: Wa-ith qulna lilmala-ikatiosjudoo li-adama fasajadoo illa ibleesa aba

data.textUthmani: فَقُلْنَا يَـٰٓـَٔادَمُ إِنَّ هَـٰذَا عَدُوٌّ لَّكَ وَلِزَوْجِكَ فَلَا يُخْرِجَنَّكُمَا مِنَ ٱلْجَنَّةِ فَتَشْقَىٰٓ
data.wordByWord: فَقُلْنَا [Then We said] يَـٰٓـَٔادَمُ [O Adam] إِنَّ [Indeed] هَـٰذَا [this] عَدُوٌّۭ [(is) an enemy] لَّكَ [to you] وَلِزَوْجِكَ [and to your wife] فَلَا [So not] يُخْرِجَنَّكُمَا [(let) him drive you both] مِنَ [from] ٱلْجَنَّةِ [Paradise] فَتَشْقَىٰٓ [so (that) you would suffer]
data.transliteration: Faqulna ya adamu innahatha AAaduwwun laka walizawjika falayukhrijannakuma mina aljannati fatashqa

data.textUthmani: إِنَّ لَكَ أَلَّا تَجُوعَ فِيهَا وَلَا تَعْرَىٰ
data.wordByWord: إِنَّ [Indeed] لَكَ [for you] أَلَّا [that not] تَجُوعَ [you will be hungry] فِيهَا [therein] وَلَا [and not] تَعْرَىٰ [you will be unclothed]
data.transliteration: Inna laka alla tajooAAa feehawala taAAra

data.textUthmani: وَأَنَّكَ لَا تَظْمَؤُا۟ فِيهَا وَلَا تَضْحَىٰ
data.wordByWord: وَأَنَّكَ [And that you] لَا [not] تَظْمَؤُا۟ [will suffer from thirst] فِيهَا [therein] وَلَا [and not] تَضْحَىٰ [exposed to the sun's heat]
data.transliteration: Waannaka la tathmaofeeha wala tadha

data.textUthmani: فَوَسْوَسَ إِلَيْهِ ٱلشَّيْطَـٰنُ قَالَ يَـٰٓـَٔادَمُ هَلْ أَدُلُّكَ عَلَىٰ شَجَرَةِ ٱلْخُلْدِ وَمُلْكٍ لَّا يَبْلَىٰ
data.wordByWord: فَوَسْوَسَ [Then whispered] إِلَيْهِ [to him] ٱلشَّيْطَـٰنُ [Shaitaan] قَالَ [he said] يَـٰٓـَٔادَمُ [O Adam] هَلْ [Shall] أَدُلُّكَ [I direct you] عَلَىٰ [to] شَجَرَةِ [(the) tree] ٱلْخُلْدِ [(of) the Eternity] وَمُلْكٍۢ [and a kingdom] لَّا [not] يَبْلَىٰ [(that will) deteriorate]
data.transliteration: Fawaswasa ilayhi ashshaytanuqala ya adamu hal adulluka AAalashajarati alkhuldi wamulkin la yabla

data.textUthmani: فَأَكَلَا مِنْهَا فَبَدَتْ لَهُمَا سَوْءَٰتُهُمَا وَطَفِقَا يَخْصِفَانِ عَلَيْهِمَا مِن وَرَقِ ٱلْجَنَّةِ ۚ وَعَصَىٰٓ ءَادَمُ رَبَّهُۥ فَغَوَىٰ
data.wordByWord: فَأَكَلَا [Then they both ate] مِنْهَا [from it] فَبَدَتْ [so became apparent] لَهُمَا [to them] سَوْءَٰتُهُمَا [their shame] وَطَفِقَا [and they began] يَخْصِفَانِ [(to) fasten] عَلَيْهِمَا [on themselves] مِن [from] وَرَقِ [(the) leaves] ٱلْجَنَّةِ ۚ [(of) Paradise] وَعَصَىٰٓ [And Adam disobeyed] ءَادَمُ [And Adam disobeyed] رَبَّهُۥ [his Lord] فَغَوَىٰ [and erred]
data.transliteration: Faakala minha fabadat lahumasaw-atuhuma watafiqa yakhsifaniAAalayhima min waraqi aljannati waAAasa adamurabbahu faghawa

data.textUthmani: ثُمَّ ٱجْتَبَـٰهُ رَبُّهُۥ فَتَابَ عَلَيْهِ وَهَدَىٰ
data.wordByWord: ثُمَّ [Then] ٱجْتَبَـٰهُ [chose him] رَبُّهُۥ [his Lord] فَتَابَ [and turned] عَلَيْهِ [to him] وَهَدَىٰ [and guided (him)]
data.transliteration: Thumma ijtabahu rabbuhu fatabaAAalayhi wahada

data.textUthmani: قَالَ ٱهْبِطَا مِنْهَا جَمِيعًۢا ۖ بَعْضُكُمْ لِبَعْضٍ عَدُوٌّ ۖ فَإِمَّا يَأْتِيَنَّكُم مِّنِّى هُدًى فَمَنِ ٱتَّبَعَ هُدَاىَ فَلَا يَضِلُّ وَلَا يَشْقَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He said] ٱهْبِطَا [Go down] مِنْهَا [from it] جَمِيعًۢا ۖ [all] بَعْضُكُمْ [some of you] لِبَعْضٍ [to others] عَدُوٌّۭ ۖ [(as) enemy] فَإِمَّا [Then if] يَأْتِيَنَّكُم [comes to you] مِّنِّى [from Me] هُدًۭى [guidance] فَمَنِ [then whoever] ٱتَّبَعَ [follows] هُدَاىَ [My guidance] فَلَا [then not] يَضِلُّ [he will go astray] وَلَا [and not] يَشْقَىٰ [suffer]
data.transliteration: Qala ihbita minhajameeAAan baAAdukum libaAAdin AAaduwwun fa-immaya/tiyannakum minnee hudan famani ittabaAAa hudaya falayadillu wala yashqa

data.textUthmani: وَمَنْ أَعْرَضَ عَن ذِكْرِى فَإِنَّ لَهُۥ مَعِيشَةً ضَنكًا وَنَحْشُرُهُۥ يَوْمَ ٱلْقِيَـٰمَةِ أَعْمَىٰ
data.wordByWord: وَمَنْ [And whoever] أَعْرَضَ [turns away] عَن [from] ذِكْرِى [My remembrance] فَإِنَّ [then indeed] لَهُۥ [for him] مَعِيشَةًۭ [(is) a life] ضَنكًۭا [straitened] وَنَحْشُرُهُۥ [and We will gather him] يَوْمَ [(on the) Day] ٱلْقِيَـٰمَةِ [(of) the Resurrection] أَعْمَىٰ [blind]
data.transliteration: Waman aAArada AAan thikreefa-inna lahu maAAeeshatan danka wanahshuruhuyawma alqiyamati aAAma

data.textUthmani: قَالَ رَبِّ لِمَ حَشَرْتَنِىٓ أَعْمَىٰ وَقَدْ كُنتُ بَصِيرًا
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He will say] رَبِّ [My Lord] لِمَ [Why] حَشَرْتَنِىٓ [You raised me] أَعْمَىٰ [blind] وَقَدْ [while [verily]] كُنتُ [I had] بَصِيرًۭا [sight]
data.transliteration: Qala rabbi lima hashartaneeaAAma waqad kuntu baseera

data.textUthmani: قَالَ كَذَٰلِكَ أَتَتْكَ ءَايَـٰتُنَا فَنَسِيتَهَا ۖ وَكَذَٰلِكَ ٱلْيَوْمَ تُنسَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قَالَ [He will say] كَذَٰلِكَ [Thus] أَتَتْكَ [came to you] ءَايَـٰتُنَا [Our Signs] فَنَسِيتَهَا ۖ [but you forgot them] وَكَذَٰلِكَ [and thus] ٱلْيَوْمَ [today] تُنسَىٰ [you will be forgotten]
data.transliteration: Qala kathalika atatka ayatunafanaseetaha wakathalika alyawma tunsa

data.textUthmani: وَكَذَٰلِكَ نَجْزِى مَنْ أَسْرَفَ وَلَمْ يُؤْمِنۢ بِـَٔايَـٰتِ رَبِّهِۦ ۚ وَلَعَذَابُ ٱلْـَٔاخِرَةِ أَشَدُّ وَأَبْقَىٰٓ
data.wordByWord: وَكَذَٰلِكَ [And thus] نَجْزِى [We recompense] مَنْ [(he) who] أَسْرَفَ [transgresses] وَلَمْ [and not] يُؤْمِنۢ [believes] بِـَٔايَـٰتِ [in (the) Signs] رَبِّهِۦ ۚ [(of) his Lord] وَلَعَذَابُ [And surely (the) punishment] ٱلْـَٔاخِرَةِ [(of) the Hereafter] أَشَدُّ [(is) more severe] وَأَبْقَىٰٓ [and more lasting]
data.transliteration: Wakathalika najzee man asrafa walamyu/min bi-ayati rabbihi walaAAathabu al-akhiratiashaddu waabqa

data.textUthmani: أَفَلَمْ يَهْدِ لَهُمْ كَمْ أَهْلَكْنَا قَبْلَهُم مِّنَ ٱلْقُرُونِ يَمْشُونَ فِى مَسَـٰكِنِهِمْ ۗ إِنَّ فِى ذَٰلِكَ لَـَٔايَـٰتٍ لِّأُو۟لِى ٱلنُّهَىٰ
data.wordByWord: أَفَلَمْ [Then has not] يَهْدِ [it guided] لَهُمْ [[for] them] كَمْ [how many] أَهْلَكْنَا [We (have) destroyed] قَبْلَهُم [before them] مِّنَ [of] ٱلْقُرُونِ [the generations] يَمْشُونَ [(as) they walk] فِى [in] مَسَـٰكِنِهِمْ ۗ [their dwellings] إِنَّ [Indeed] فِى [in] ذَٰلِكَ [that] لَـَٔايَـٰتٍۢ [surely (are) Signs] لِّأُو۟لِى [for possessors] ٱلنُّهَىٰ [(of) intelligence]
data.transliteration: Afalam yahdi lahum kam ahlaknaqablahum mina alqurooni yamshoona fee masakinihim inna feethalika laayatin li-olee annuha

data.textUthmani: وَلَوْلَا كَلِمَةٌ سَبَقَتْ مِن رَّبِّكَ لَكَانَ لِزَامًا وَأَجَلٌ مُّسَمًّى
data.wordByWord: وَلَوْلَا [And if not] كَلِمَةٌۭ [(for) a Word] سَبَقَتْ [(that) preceded] مِن [from] رَّبِّكَ [your Lord] لَكَانَ [surely (would) have been] لِزَامًۭا [an obligation] وَأَجَلٌۭ [and a term] مُّسَمًّۭى [determined]
data.transliteration: Walawla kalimatun sabaqat minrabbika lakana lizaman waajalun musamma

data.textUthmani: فَٱصْبِرْ عَلَىٰ مَا يَقُولُونَ وَسَبِّحْ بِحَمْدِ رَبِّكَ قَبْلَ طُلُوعِ ٱلشَّمْسِ وَقَبْلَ غُرُوبِهَا ۖ وَمِنْ ءَانَآئِ ٱلَّيْلِ فَسَبِّحْ وَأَطْرَافَ ٱلنَّهَارِ لَعَلَّكَ تَرْضَىٰ
data.wordByWord: فَٱصْبِرْ [So be patient] عَلَىٰ [over] مَا [what] يَقُولُونَ [they say] وَسَبِّحْ [and glorify] بِحَمْدِ [with praise] رَبِّكَ [(of) your Lord] قَبْلَ [before] طُلُوعِ [(the) rising] ٱلشَّمْسِ [(of) the sun] وَقَبْلَ [and before] غُرُوبِهَا ۖ [its setting] وَمِنْ [and from] ءَانَآئِ [(the) hours] ٱلَّيْلِ [(of) the night] فَسَبِّحْ [and glorify] وَأَطْرَافَ [(at the) ends] ٱلنَّهَارِ [(of) the day] لَعَلَّكَ [so that you may] تَرْضَىٰ [be satisfied]
data.transliteration: Fasbir AAala mayaqooloona wasabbih bihamdi rabbika qabla tulooAAiashshamsi waqabla ghuroobiha wamin ana-iallayli fasabbih waatrafa annaharilaAAallaka tarda

data.textUthmani: وَلَا تَمُدَّنَّ عَيْنَيْكَ إِلَىٰ مَا مَتَّعْنَا بِهِۦٓ أَزْوَٰجًا مِّنْهُمْ زَهْرَةَ ٱلْحَيَوٰةِ ٱلدُّنْيَا لِنَفْتِنَهُمْ فِيهِ ۚ وَرِزْقُ رَبِّكَ خَيْرٌ وَأَبْقَىٰ
data.wordByWord: وَلَا [And (do) not] تَمُدَّنَّ [extend] عَيْنَيْكَ [your eyes] إِلَىٰ [towards] مَا [what] مَتَّعْنَا [We have given for enjoyment] بِهِۦٓ [[with it]] أَزْوَٰجًۭا [pairs] مِّنْهُمْ [of them] زَهْرَةَ [(the) splendor] ٱلْحَيَوٰةِ [(of) the life] ٱلدُّنْيَا [(of) the world] لِنَفْتِنَهُمْ [that We may test them] فِيهِ ۚ [in it] وَرِزْقُ [And (the) provision] رَبِّكَ [(of) your Lord] خَيْرٌۭ [(is) better] وَأَبْقَىٰ [and more lasting]
data.transliteration: Wala tamuddanna AAaynayka ilama mattaAAna bihi azwajan minhum zahrata alhayatiaddunya linaftinahum feehi warizqu rabbika khayrunwaabqa

data.textUthmani: وَأْمُرْ أَهْلَكَ بِٱلصَّلَوٰةِ وَٱصْطَبِرْ عَلَيْهَا ۖ لَا نَسْـَٔلُكَ رِزْقًا ۖ نَّحْنُ نَرْزُقُكَ ۗ وَٱلْعَـٰقِبَةُ لِلتَّقْوَىٰ
data.wordByWord: وَأْمُرْ [And enjoin] أَهْلَكَ [(on) your family] بِٱلصَّلَوٰةِ [the prayer] وَٱصْطَبِرْ [and be steadfast] عَلَيْهَا ۖ [therein] لَا [Not] نَسْـَٔلُكَ [We ask you] رِزْقًۭا ۖ [(for) provision] نَّحْنُ [We] نَرْزُقُكَ ۗ [provide (for) you] وَٱلْعَـٰقِبَةُ [and the outcome] لِلتَّقْوَىٰ [(is) for the righteous[ness]]
data.transliteration: Wa/mur ahlaka bissalatiwastabir AAalayha la nas-alukarizqan nahnu narzuquka walAAaqibatu littaqwa

data.textUthmani: وَقَالُوا۟ لَوْلَا يَأْتِينَا بِـَٔايَةٍ مِّن رَّبِّهِۦٓ ۚ أَوَلَمْ تَأْتِهِم بَيِّنَةُ مَا فِى ٱلصُّحُفِ ٱلْأُولَىٰ
data.wordByWord: وَقَالُوا۟ [And they say] لَوْلَا [Why not] يَأْتِينَا [he brings us] بِـَٔايَةٍۢ [a sign] مِّن [from] رَّبِّهِۦٓ ۚ [his Lord] أَوَلَمْ [Has not] تَأْتِهِم [come to them] بَيِّنَةُ [evidence] مَا [(of) what] فِى [(was) in] ٱلصُّحُفِ [the Scriptures] ٱلْأُولَىٰ [the former]
data.transliteration: Waqaloo lawla ya/teenabi-ayatin min rabbihi awa lam ta/tihim bayyinatu mafee assuhufi al-oola

data.textUthmani: وَلَوْ أَنَّآ أَهْلَكْنَـٰهُم بِعَذَابٍ مِّن قَبْلِهِۦ لَقَالُوا۟ رَبَّنَا لَوْلَآ أَرْسَلْتَ إِلَيْنَا رَسُولًا فَنَتَّبِعَ ءَايَـٰتِكَ مِن قَبْلِ أَن نَّذِلَّ وَنَخْزَىٰ
data.wordByWord: وَلَوْ [And if] أَنَّآ [We] أَهْلَكْنَـٰهُم [(had) destroyed them] بِعَذَابٍۢ [with a punishment] مِّن [before him] قَبْلِهِۦ [before him] لَقَالُوا۟ [surely they (would) have said] رَبَّنَا [Our Lord] لَوْلَآ [why not] أَرْسَلْتَ [You sent] إِلَيْنَا [to us] رَسُولًۭا [a Messenger] فَنَتَّبِعَ [so we (could) have followed] ءَايَـٰتِكَ [Your signs] مِن [before] قَبْلِ [before] أَن [[that]] نَّذِلَّ [we were humiliated] وَنَخْزَىٰ [and disgraced]
data.transliteration: Walaw anna ahlaknahum biAAathabinmin qablihi laqaloo rabbana lawla arsaltailayna rasoolan fanattabiAAa ayatika minqabli an nathilla wanakhza

data.textUthmani: قُلْ كُلٌّ مُّتَرَبِّصٌ فَتَرَبَّصُوا۟ ۖ فَسَتَعْلَمُونَ مَنْ أَصْحَـٰبُ ٱلصِّرَٰطِ ٱلسَّوِىِّ وَمَنِ ٱهْتَدَىٰ
data.wordByWord: قُلْ [Say] كُلٌّۭ [Each] مُّتَرَبِّصٌۭ [(is) waiting] فَتَرَبَّصُوا۟ ۖ [so await] فَسَتَعْلَمُونَ [Then you will know] مَنْ [who] أَصْحَـٰبُ [(are the) companions] ٱلصِّرَٰطِ [(of) the way] ٱلسَّوِىِّ [[the] even] وَمَنِ [and who] ٱهْتَدَىٰ [is guided]
data.transliteration: Qul kullun mutarabbisun fatarabbasoofasataAAlamoona man as-habu assiratiassawiyyi wamani ihtada
